  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Effective reintegration into education and family life (South Africa)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Beaufort West and Uitsig, both in the Western Cape, have high levels of poverty, unemployment, violence, drug and alcohol abuse, and HIV infection. Because of this, many parents are unable to care for or protect their children. This can lead to children dropping out of school and getting involved with gangs, dangerous sexual behaviour or the abuse of alcohol and drugs. This project will help children back into school, and work with teachers and parents to prevent other children from dropping out. Members of the community will build trust with street children and their families, making sure they can read, write and count. For the worst affected families, children and their mothers will get emergency shelter and counselling. Intensive family therapy will work to bring about long term change.</narrative>
  </description>
